---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About BES3" description="The editorial principles behind BES3.">
  <section class="page-hero shell">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">ABOUT BES3</p><h1>Clearer beauty, with the method left in.</h1>
    </div><p class="lede">
      BES3 is an independent editorial platform for people who want to understand a beauty choice
      before making it.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="section reading-width article-body">
    <h2>What we publish</h2>
    <p>
      We cover skincare, makeup, hair care, fragrance and the product categories within them. Our
      goal is not to create another shelf of hype; it is to make the shelf easier to navigate.
    </p>
    <h2>How we work</h2>
    <p>
      Every article has an author, sources and a review date. We distinguish a brand's claim from
      independent evidence and from our own editorial judgment. When information is uncertain, we
      say so.
    </p>
    <h2>Commercial relationships</h2>
    <p>
      BES3 may use selected affiliate links, including within our Brand Focus features. A commercial
      relationship does not buy an editorial conclusion. Disclosures sit near the link, and
      sponsored work is labelled separately.
    </p>
    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>
      Found an error or an outdated detail? Email <a href="mailto:editorial@bes3.com"
        >editorial@bes3.com</a
      > with the page URL and a source. We keep a visible updated date and correct material errors promptly.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
